description: Borrowed from Middle French détracter, from Latin detractum, past participle of detraho.

verbs.description: detract (third-person singular simple present detracts, present participle detracting, simple past and past participle detracted)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To take away; to withdraw or remove.
(transitive) To take credit or reputation from; to defame or decry.
examples: That calumnious critic  […]  / Detracting what laboriously we do.
